  "market_context": "Intraday session following a 4-hour reversal candle with large wick; analyst waited for lower-time-frame confirmation (change in state of delivery) before entering long continuations, using protected swings and fair value gaps as POIs.",
  "key_observation": "The 4-hour chart showed a reversal candle (C2 closure), but the analyst avoided trading the initial reversal and instead waited for 15-minute change in state of delivery and consolidation breakout to confirm continuation higher.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the 4-hour reversal candle (C2 closure) with large wick, indicating no immediate expansion—only a setup for continuation.",
    "Step 2: On the 15-minute chart, wait for price to close over the series of down-close candles to confirm change in state of delivery (CISD).",
    "Step 3: After CISD confirmation, observe shallow retracement into a fair value gap (POI) and formation of protected swings on the 15-minute timeframe.",
    "Step 4: Trade continuation long after price retests the protected swing/FVG zone and closes above the mean threshold, targeting liquidity above (e.g., prior high or day’s high).",
    "Step 5: Repeat the same fractal process on lower time frames (3-minute) for precise entry: wait for C2 closure, then CISD, then retest of FVG/protected swing for C3/C4 continuation."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade hit 2R target successfully after multiple continuations aligned across 4H → 15m → 3m timeframes.",
  "lessons": "Always trade continuations—not reversals—after higher-time-frame reversal candles. Confirmation via change in state of delivery on lower time frames is mandatory. Protected swings and fair value gaps serve as high-probability entry zones for multi-timeframe alignment.",
